<title type="html"><![CDATA[Easy to understand NES emulator source-code]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8904&amp;p=93964#p93964"><![CDATA[
No matter what emulator you look at it is going to be pretty complex. The best way to understand it is to write you own. The basic operation of emulation can be this.<br /><br />Write a CPU Core for the 65xx variant in the NES. Basically a 6502 but no decimal mode. Create your memory handlers and implement some sort of PPU, then alternate running the CPU and PPU. <br /><br />It would be more helpful if you said what specifically you are looking to do.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Thu May 17, 2012 9:51 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
